      "comment": "ULTIMATE WARRIOR (8) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 3.5 lengths at this track in a handy 23.75 beating Docherty. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Can make it two on the bounce. JETSTREAM ICON (2) had a tough draw to overcome and was game in defeat when only 2 lengths from Matt Loch in second (22.40) at Geelong. Must be included in calculations. BAROOGA KING (4) has a strong winning strike-rate here with three wins and a placing from seven tries. In the money last time at Shepparton (25.49) in a Grade 5, finishing a neck second. With even luck and a clean start should be thereabouts. PAW XANTIPPE (7) has strong credentials over this journey.",
